Package bio.singa.mathematics.concepts

Interface Subtractable<NumberConcept extends Subtractable<NumberConcept>>

  • Type Parameters:
    NumberConcept - A reference to the class or interface which the subtraction will result in.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabeledMatrix<LabelType>, Matrix, Quaternion, Ring<RingType>, Vector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DoubleInterval, IntegerInterval, LabeledRegularMatrix, LabeledSymmetricMatrix, RegularMatrix, RegularQuaternion, RegularVector, Scalar, SquareMatrix, SymmetricMatrix, Vector2D, Vector3D
    public interface Subtractable<NumberConcept extends Subtractable<NumberConcept>>
    The "subtraction" operation can be any anticommutative and not associative binary operation on a number concept.

    It is anticommutative, meaning that changing the order changes the result. It is not associative, meaning that when one subtracts more than two numbers, the order in which subtraction is performed matters. Subtraction of the "Additive Zero Element" does not change a number.

    See Also:
    Wikipedia: Subtraction

      • subtract

        NumberConcept subtract​(NumberConcept subtrahend)
        Subtracts the given Object (called subtrahend) from this Object (called minuend) and returns a new Object (called difference). Neither subtrahend nor minuend shall be changed.
        Parameters:
        subtrahend - Another object.
        Returns:
        The difference between this object and the given subtrahend objects.
